FBIS4-1121 "drafr078_c_94002" FBIS-AFR-94-078 Daily Report 21 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA IEC Rules Out Another Party Joining Elections IEC Rules Out Another Party Joining Elections MB2104193094 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1600 GMT 21 Apr 94 MB2104193094 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] The Independent Electoral Commission [IEC] has ruled out the possibility of another party joining the election. The chairman of the IEC, Mr. Justice Johann Kriegler, said in Johannesburg that if the CP [Conservative Party] reached an agreement on entering the election, the IEC would be prepared to count votes for the Freedom Front separately in some areas. An IEC spokesman added that by four o'clock this afternoon the IFP [Inkatha Freedom Party] had still not submitted its candidates lists.
